===Glyph origin===
{{Han etym}}
{{liushu|p}}. According to Shuowen Jiezi, it's an animal paw with spread toes, hence the character is linked to [[蹯]].

According to Zhang Shichao (張世超), it's the representation of a wooden plough ([[力]]) and some seeds to convey the concept of "disseminate, spread", hence the character is linked to [[播]].

Unrelated to the top component of [[𢍏]], used in [[奧]].

===Etymology===
Exopassive of {{och-l|辨|id=2|to divide, distinguish, discriminate}}; possibly in the same word-family as another exopassive {{och-l|瓣|what is divided}}. These three thus may be related to either {{och-l|班|to distribute → to arrange, classify → class, group}} or {{cog|lus|pʰel||to split, cut in halves}} (with medial *{{IPAfont|-r-}} dropped after labial initials according to Mizo phonotactics) ({{zh-ref|Schuessler, 2007}}).

